  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ecobank CAR</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ecobank Centrafrique (&quot;Ecobank&quot; or the &quot;Bank&quot;) is the leading bank in Central African Republic with over 45% market share in terms of total assets and over 53,000 clients. Ecobank offers a variety of banking products to its corporate, SMEs as well as retail clients. The proposed project will provide local currency financing to the Bank to enable it to extend medium-term funding to its SME clients which is one of IFCs key responses to assist in mitigating the effects of currency risk by providing medium term financing in local currency to support the Banks lending activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFCs investment in Ecobank is expected to deliver a strong development impact mainly by leveraging on the scope and reach of the Bank to increase access to finance for the underserved SME segment, and thus speeding up economic growth.</narrative>
  </description>
